Both gastown and beads test suites spawn test dolt-server processes that are not cleaned up when tests complete. Found 31 zombie dolt sql-server processes on random ports with /tmp data dirs after a swarm of polecats ran tests. Each zombie uses ~7-20MB RAM. Tests should register cleanup via t.Cleanup() or defer to kill their test servers. The testdoltserver.go already has shutdown logic but it's not being called reliably.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"steve.yegge@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-28T03:58:54Z","created_by":"mayor","updated_at":"2026-02-28T06:03:06Z"}

